					h2 What are Quantity Queries?
				section.content
					h3 A quantity query is a CSS selector that allows styles to be applied to elements based on the number of siblings. 
					h4 At Least
					p Styles are applied to all elements when there are <strong>at least</strong> 5 number of items and siblings present.
					code .item:nth-last-child(n+5):first-child, .item:nth-last-child(n+5):first-child ~ .item {}
					h4 At Most
					p Styles are applied to all elements when there are <strong>at most</strong>  10 items and siblings present.
					code .item:nth-last-child(-n+10):first-child, .item:nth-last-child(-n+10):first-child ~ .item { }
					h4 Between
					p The best of both worlds. Styles are applied when the number of elements is <strong>between</strong> 3 and 5.
					code .item:nth-last-child(n+3):nth-last-child(-n+5):first-child, .item:nth-last-child(-n+3):nth-last-child(-n+5):first-child ~ .item { }
